{'BugID': 'MATH-836', 'Summary': 'Fraction(double, int) constructor strange behaviour', 'Description': 'The Fraction constructor Fraction(double, int) takes a double value and a int maximal denominator, and approximates a fraction. When the double value is a large, negative number with many digits in the fractional part, and the maximal denominator is a big, positive integer (in the 100'000s), two distinct bugs can manifest:

